hopobject.body: I've come to collect a parcel gmedu.org Craft beer now makes up 6.5 percent of U.S. beer sales by volume (10.2 percent by dollars), with an estimated 13.2 million barrels having been sold in 2012. That’s a growth of more than 46 percent since 2006, when 7.1 million barrels were sold. Sales for the big domestic, non-craft brands have remained relatively flat, with 2012 numbers being nearly identical to those in 2008.
